  "title": "Desolatum",
  "description": "A relatively minor decorative expansion for The End dimension",
  "body": "<div class=\"box p-4 pb-2 project-detail__content\" data-user-content>\n        <p style=\"text-align:center\"><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/L9wNywS.png\" alt=\"desolatum title\" width=\"4096\" height=\"666\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left\"><img style=\"float:right\" src=\"https://storage.ko-fi.com/cdn/useruploads/display/db181bc6-8b42-4b2f-8d87-503b2ba0335e_desolatum_black_smith_skin.png\" alt=\"end dunes blacksmith has a message for you!\" width=\"208\" height=\"245\"><strong>Blacksmith's Note: </strong>Desolatum aims to add more decorative content to the End dimension, while also revamping many of the dimension's already existing textures. With that being said, some content may change between the alpha/beta stage of development and the official non-beta release. Furthermore, there's more content planned to be added in the future, some in the pre-existing content of the mod and entirely new sections of features!</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left\">&nbsp;</p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Biomes</strong></h1>\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>(Screenshots taken with BSL Shaders + modified settings enabled)</strong></p>\n<hr>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/albkWL0.png\" alt=\"end dunes description\" width=\"750\" height=\"423\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/K3f6U8i.png\" alt=\"obsidised end highlands description\" width=\"750\" height=\"422\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left\"><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/ojVoRyE.png\" alt=\"viridian highlands description\" width=\"750\" height=\"422\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left\">&nbsp;</p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Built-in Resource Pack Differences</strong></h1>\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>(These textures are optional/can be changed by disabling or enabling the resource pack(s))</strong></p>\n<hr>\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>The end, as a whole, has been adjusted to not be as bright and a bit less saturated.</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/7QIPbqR.png\" alt=\"resourcepack difference 0\" width=\"750\" height=\"391\"></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Purpur has gotten a texture revamp + additional variants!</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/oEIqjSf.png\" alt=\"resourcepack difference 1\" width=\"750\" height=\"391\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/3uYp2dQ.png\" alt=\"resourcepack difference 2\" width=\"750\" height=\"391\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Obsidian has also gotten a texture revamp!</strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left\"><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/oqkw70b.png\" alt=\"resourcepack difference 3\" width=\"750\" height=\"391\"></p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Compatibility</strong></h1>\n<hr>\n<p>Compatibility recipes are available for Create, Create: Sifting, Create: Dragon's Plus, and Oritech machines! Allowing automation for otherwise non-automatable blocks/items or completely new ways of obtaining certain blocks/items!</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto\" src=\"https://i.imgur.com/MIB37ZI.png\" alt=\"compatibility recipes\" width=\"750\" height=\"338\"></p>\n    </div>",
